# Action Button Style

Any page or section that shows **action buttons** (e.g. in table Action columns or list item actions) MUST follow this same pattern for consistency.

## Structure

- Wrap each action in: `<div className="hs-tooltip ti-main-tooltip">`
- Button/link has: `className="hs-tooltip-toggle ti-btn ti-btn-icon ti-btn-sm ti-btn-{color}"`
- Tooltip is a sibling span:  
  `<span className="hs-tooltip-content ti-main-tooltip-content py-1 px-2 !bg-black !text-xs !font-medium !text-white shadow-sm dark:bg-slate-700" role="tooltip">Label</span>`

## Color variants

- **View / Login as**: `ti-btn-success` (green)
- **Edit**: `ti-btn-info` (blue)
- **Delete**: `ti-btn-danger` (red)
- Use other `ti-btn-*` variants only when the action is clearly different (e.g. warning for a caution action).

## Icons

Use Remix Icon classes (`ri-*-line`) consistently:

- View: `ri-eye-line`
- Login as (impersonation): `ri-login-box-line`
- Edit: `ri-pencil-line`
- Delete: `ri-delete-bin-line`

## Example (single action)

```tsx
<div className="hs-tooltip ti-main-tooltip">
  <button
    type="button"
    onClick={() => handleView(row)}
    className="hs-tooltip-toggle ti-btn ti-btn-icon ti-btn-sm ti-btn-success"
  >
    <i className="ri-eye-line"></i>
    <span className="hs-tooltip-content ti-main-tooltip-content py-1 px-2 !bg-black !text-xs !font-medium !text-white shadow-sm dark:bg-slate-700" role="tooltip">
      View
    </span>
  </button>
</div>
```

## Container

Group action buttons in: `<div className="flex items-center justify-center gap-2">` (or `gap-1` if tighter).

Reference implementation: `app/(components)/(contentlayout)/settings/users/page.tsx` (Users table Action column).
